msContents.summary: Contains Jacques de Vitry's narration of events in the Holy Land in the time of the crusades, with a short treatise on the Eucharist. Also included is a spurious sermon by Augustine; a letter on the institution of anchorites and a treatise on the eremitical life, both attributed to Basil of Caesarea; two descriptions of the Holy Land (the first by Rorgo Fretellus; the second is spuriously attributed to Eugippius); and an unknown work attributed to Rorgo Fretellus.

msItem.title: Tractatus beati Augustini episcopi de misera uita corporis et anime
msItem.incipit: O uita que tantos decepisti, tantos seduxisti ... [f. 1r]
msItem.explicit: ... domino nostro Iesu Christo qui cum Patre et Spiritu sancto regnat per infinita secula seculorum. Amen. [f. 4r-4v]

msItem.title: Epistola Basilii Cesarienisis episcopi ad Gregorium [s] Nazanzenum super institutione anachoritarum ...
msItem.incipit: Agnoui literas tuas, ut enim qui amicorum filios ex ingenita quam per se ferunt ... [f. 4v]
msItem.explicit: ... cum gemitu et lacrimis diuinum adiutorium ad ea perficienda, que studiose proponit. Deo gratias. [f. 9v]

msItem.title: Tractatus beati Basilii episcopi de uita solitaria
msItem.incipit: Libet inter cetera de singularis vite meritis pauca perstringere ... [f. 10r]
msItem.explicit: ... ad habitacionem perueniet domus non manufacte sed in celis eterne, sociatus angelicis choris, ipso prestante qui est cum Patre et Spiritu sancto Deus benedictus in secula. Amen. [f. 13r]

msItem.title: Descriptio terre sancte, archidyaconus Antiochenus
msItem.incipit: Domino suo uenerabili et fratri in Domino R. Dei gratia Toletano comiti R. Fretellus eadem gratia archidiaconus Antiochie ... [f. 14r]
msItem.explicit: ... noticiam querere dignatus es, prout sanius potero, sublimitati tue diligenter elucidare non dedignabor. [f. 14v]

msItem.title: Vertamus eya stilum nostrum sumentes inicium ab Hebron ...
Vertamus eya stilum nostrum sumentes inicium ab Hebron que et Hebron. Hebron olim metropolis ... [f. 14v]
msItem.explicit: ... Dauid dicitur Ioseph attestante fabricauit eamque Antoniam uocauit. [f. 25v]

msItem.title: Prologus magistri Iacobi de Vitriaco, Canon. Regularis Episcop. Acconensis, super historiam Iherosolymitanam
msItem.incipit: Postquam diuine propitiacionis munificiencia exercitus christiani longamitatem et patiencia clementer respiciens ... [f. 26r]
msItem.explicit: ... ad confutacionem infidelium et confusionem impiorum hominum et ad laudem et imitationem bonorum, diligens lector manifeste poterit perpendere. [f. 27v]

msItem.title: [Historia Orientalis, liber primus]
msItem.incipit: Terra sancta promissionis Deo amabilis et sanctis angelis uenerabilis et uniuerso mundo admirabilis ... [f. 29r]
msItem.explicit: ... a Deo et sancta Romana ecclesia consolacionem et subsidium de die in diem expectantes. [f. 133v]

msItem.title: [Liber] secundus in cuius parte prima occidentalium breuiter narratur primum capitulum de corrupcione occidentalis regionis et de ecclesiis occidentalium
msItem.incipit: Dum igitur orientalis ecclesia que quondam a finibus terre uenit audire sapienciam Salomonis ... [f. 134r]
msItem.explicit: ... sed propter uestustatem forme, singulis [septi]manis renouanda sunt sacramenta. [f. 213r]

supportDesc.extent: Leaves ii + 213 (1-12 (paper), 13 (vellum), 14-212 (paper)) + ii; 215 x 145 mm bound to 230 x 160 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 33 long lines (dimensions of written space: 145 x 85 mm); frame ruled; marginalia throughout.

decoDesc.decoNote: Four pen-flourished initials, two of which are decorated in red and green, leaves 1r, 14r, 26r and 134r.
